6.4.0.description:
## 6.4.0 Changes
- Reordered the code of the World.py hook to be more in AP's specs
- Fix disabling DLC items/locs
- Made the code respect all the Unit test
- Ensured all the fuzz tests didn't end in failure
## 6.3.0 Changes
- A basic WIP suitless logic (via option)
- A new  item that locks you from moving the ship (also an option)
- Moved and renamed some of the regions
  - made it so teleporter logic work better
    - Added an option to enable untested reverse teleporter logic (which require a mod that I dont think exists out of the main randomizer)
- Made Hide & seek a signal but split winning the game from it (~~taken~~~~stolen~~ inspired from main)
- removed Eye photos is now just photos


Do report any bugs/issues either on [Github](https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApworlds/issues) or on Discord
**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApworlds/commits/6.4.0

v4.0.0.description:
# Known issue with this .apworld file: if you want to generate a game with it you have to unzip it
## NEW OPTIONS
* Added options to the player.yaml
  * goal: choose where you want your game to end
  * randomized_content: choose what part of the game you want to play (base game, dlc or both)
  * require_solanum & require_prisoner: enable requiring either/both to win
  * do_place_item_category(default true): should some items be preplaced localy to help with the flow of the game
## New Goals:
if imposible combined with randomized_content will go back to standard
- standard(default): for dlc only will end on prisoner, for base and base+dlc will end at the eye.
- eye: Will require going to the eye.
- prisoner: Will end after talking to the prisonner
- visit_all_archive: Will End by visiting all the archive in a single loop without being caught
- ash_twin_project_break_spacetime: Require going to the ash twin project and break spacetime there.
- high_energy_lab_break_spacetime: Require going to the high energy lab and break spacetime there.
- stuck_with_solanum: Get the Adv. warp core to Solanum and wait for Credits.
- stuck_in_stranger: Get the Adv. warp core to the Stranger and wait for Credits.
- stuck_in_dream: Get the Adv. warp core to the Stranger and die to get to the Dreamworld.
## What's Changed
* Working DLC selector by @axxroytovu in https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApWorlds/pull/1
* Merge the dlc to the base game with the new Content options by @nicopop in https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApWorlds/pull/2

## New Contributors
* @axxroytovu made their first contribution in https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApWorlds/pull/1
* @nicopop made their first contribution in https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApWorlds/pull/2

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nicopop/ManualApWorlds/compare/v3.2.1...v4.0.0

## Attached to this apworld is 2 yaml:

- Standard difficulty (player.yaml)
- Long version: force you to visit Solanum and Prisoner if you dont disable dlc
v4.0.0.title: Outer Wilds Apworld v4 Now Customizable!
